support Dark Mode using an

00:01:03.506 --> 00:01:04.866 A:middle
example application that they

00:01:04.866 --> 00:01:05.426 A:middle
built together.

00:01:06.156 --> 00:01:07.016 A:middle
The three of us are super

00:01:07.016 --> 00:01:08.016 A:middle
excited to share all of these

00:01:08.066 --> 00:01:09.246 A:middle
details with all of you, so

00:01:09.426 --> 00:01:10.086 A:middle
let's jump right in.

00:01:10.886 --> 00:01:13.086 A:middle
As we announced in yesterday's

00:01:13.116 --> 00:01:15.316 A:middle
keynote, macOS 10.14 is going to

00:01:15.316 --> 00:01:16.896 A:middle
be getting a new interface

00:01:16.896 --> 00:01:19.186 A:middle
appearance, and we call it Dark

00:01:19.186 --> 00:01:19.416 A:middle
Mode.

00:01:20.416 --> 00:01:22.146 A:middle
The new design is very

00:01:22.216 --> 00:01:24.466 A:middle
attractive and engaging, while

00:01:24.466 --> 00:01:26.036 A:middle
at the same time being very calm

00:01:26.076 --> 00:01:26.806 A:middle
and understated.

00:01:27.366 --> 00:01:28.566 A:middle
These are great qualities for an

00:01:28.566 --> 00:01:29.626 A:middle
interface, and they make it

00:01:29.626 --> 00:01:31.266 A:middle
great for creative professionals

00:01:31.556 --> 00:01:33.076 A:middle
who are dealing with heavily

00:01:33.136 --> 00:01:34.906 A:middle
detailed images and colorful

00:01:34.906 --> 00:01:37.516 A:middle
assets such as images and video

00:01:37.516 --> 00:01:37.896 A:middle
assets.

00:01:38.736 --> 00:01:40.966 A:middle
But, in actuality, it's actually

00:01:40.966 --> 00:01:42.536 A:middle
great for just about any type of

00:01:42.596 --> 00:01:44.526 A:middle
user who is looking to

00:01:44.526 --> 00:01:46.326 A:middle
concentrate or focus on any

00:01:46.326 --> 00:01:47.376 A:middle
given task at hand.

00:01:47.976 --> 00:01:48.936 A:middle
So, whether you're trying to

00:01:48.936 --> 00:01:50.396 A:middle
concentrate on writing the next

00:01:50.396 --> 00:01:52.856 A:middle
great novel or you're trying to

00:01:52.896 --> 00:01:54.146 A:middle
read one without disturbing your

00:01:54.146 --> 00:01:56.136 A:middle
bedside partner, Dark Mode is

00:01:56.136 --> 00:01:57.486 A:middle
really great for either type of

00:01:57.486 --> 00:01:58.156 A:middle
situation.


00:02:03.246 --> 00:02:05.686 A:middle
The interface shares a lot of

00:02:05.856 --> 00:02:07.166 A:middle
family resemblances between the

00:02:07.166 --> 00:02:08.496 A:middle
light appearance and the dark

00:02:08.496 --> 00:02:09.846 A:middle
appearance, and that is because

00:02:09.846 --> 00:02:11.246 A:middle
we wanted to encourage users to

00:02:11.246 --> 00:02:13.066 A:middle
switch between both appearances

00:02:13.436 --> 00:02:16.116 A:middle
easily and find the one that

00:02:16.116 --> 00:02:17.386 A:middle
really best suits their needs.

00:02:17.816 --> 00:02:18.896 A:middle
And so it was very important

00:02:18.896 --> 00:02:19.876 A:middle
that things like control

00:02:19.876 --> 00:02:22.216 A:middle
metrics, window layout, and the

00:02:22.296 --> 00:02:24.186 A:middle
distribution of translucent

00:02:24.186 --> 00:02:25.826 A:middle
materials be the same as much as

00:02:25.826 --> 00:02:26.746 A:middle
possible between both

00:02:26.746 --> 00:02:27.436 A:middle
appearances.

00:02:28.246 --> 00:02:30.056 A:middle
As such it's also equally

00:02:30.056 --> 00:02:31.166 A:middle
important that all of your

00:02:31.166 --> 00:02:33.446 A:middle
applications take full advantage

00:02:33.446 --> 00:02:35.316 A:middle
of both appearances so that they

00:02:35.316 --> 00:02:37.156 A:middle
update correctly between both

00:02:37.356 --> 00:02:38.996 A:middle
appearances no matter what the

00:02:38.996 --> 00:02:40.716 A:middle
system is running under.

00:02:40.716 --> 00:02:41.796 A:middle
You really don't want to be that

00:02:41.876 --> 00:02:42.956 A:middle
one light appearance that's

00:02:43.276 --> 00:02:46.066 A:middle
stuck in dark appearance.

00:02:46.176 --> 00:02:47.656 A:middle
All in all, we're super happy

00:02:47.656 --> 00:02:49.226 A:middle
with how the design turned out,

00:02:49.226 --> 00:02:51.196 A:middle
and we are really anxious to see

00:02:51.196 --> 00:02:53.286 A:middle
what you guys are going to turn

00:02:53.286 --> 00:02:54.576 A:middle
your apps into as soon as you

00:02:54.576 --> 00:02:55.796 A:middle
get hands on the developer beta

00:02:55.796 --> 00:02:56.896 A:middle
and start adopting the Dark

00:02:56.896 --> 00:02:57.136 A:middle
Mode.

00:02:59.206 --> 00:03:01.386 A:middle
Aside from Dark Mode, another


00:02:59.206 --> 00:03:01.386 A:middle
Aside from Dark Mode, another

00:03:01.386 --> 00:03:02.866 A:middle
new interface feature that we

00:03:02.866 --> 00:03:04.966 A:middle
added into macOS 10.14 are

00:03:05.026 --> 00:03:05.866 A:middle
accent colors.

00:03:06.466 --> 00:03:08.036 A:middle
Previous releases of macOS

00:03:08.536 --> 00:03:10.376 A:middle
offered two accent colors, blue

00:03:10.376 --> 00:03:12.196 A:middle
and graphite, but for macOS

00:03:12.196 --> 00:03:13.876 A:middle
10.14, we've expanded the color

00:03:13.876 --> 00:03:15.266 A:middle
palette to include eight fun

00:03:15.266 --> 00:03:16.556 A:middle
colors to really help you

00:03:16.556 --> 00:03:18.756 A:middle
personalize your Mac.

00:03:18.816 --> 00:03:20.926 A:middle
So, if you're like me and you

00:03:21.186 --> 00:03:22.556 A:middle
love the color red, you're going

00:03:22.556 --> 00:03:23.696 A:middle
to immediately switch over to

00:03:23.696 --> 00:03:25.596 A:middle
the color red [laughs].

00:03:25.856 --> 00:03:30.016 A:middle
If orange or yellow are more of

00:03:30.016 --> 00:03:31.456 A:middle
your preference, you're going to

00:03:31.456 --> 00:03:32.286 A:middle
switch over to those, and we

00:03:32.286 --> 00:03:34.316 A:middle
make those available as well.

00:03:34.316 --> 00:03:38.256 A:middle
I should note that the accent

00:03:38.256 --> 00:03:39.336 A:middle
colors are not just a

00:03:39.336 --> 00:03:41.376 A:middle
sub-feature of Dark Mode, but

00:03:41.376 --> 00:03:42.626 A:middle
they're also available in Light

00:03:42.626 --> 00:03:42.896 A:middle
Mode.

00:03:43.016 --> 00:03:44.986 A:middle
So if you prefer Light Mode but

00:03:44.986 --> 00:03:46.626 A:middle
want green accent color, you can

00:03:46.626 --> 00:03:47.316 A:middle
do that as well.

00:03:49.286 --> 00:03:50.316 A:middle
So, now that we've covered a

00:03:50.316 --> 00:03:51.856 A:middle
little bit of the basics of what

00:03:52.246 --> 00:03:53.896 A:middle
Dark Mode is and what accent

00:03:53.896 --> 00:03:55.616 A:middle
colors are also, let's dive a

00:03:55.616 --> 00:03:56.696 A:middle
little bit deeper into some of

00:03:56.696 --> 00:03:58.006 A:middle
the design principles that went

00:03:58.006 --> 00:03:58.806 A:middle
into Dark Mode.

00:03:59.446 --> 00:04:01.686 A:middle
At Apple, when we begin a new


00:03:59.446 --> 00:04:01.686 A:middle
At Apple, when we begin a new

00:04:01.686 --> 00:04:02.916 A:middle
design project, we like to

00:04:02.916 --> 00:04:04.326 A:middle
establish a set of design

00:04:04.326 --> 00:04:05.456 A:middle
principles to help guide us

00:04:05.516 --> 00:04:06.476 A:middle
throughout the entire design

00:04:06.476 --> 00:04:06.996 A:middle
process.

00:04:07.656 --> 00:04:09.506 A:middle
And, with Dark Mode, there were

00:04:09.506 --> 00:04:11.426 A:middle
three in particular that we

00:04:11.426 --> 00:04:12.786 A:middle
referred to quite often

00:04:13.496 --> 00:04:14.606 A:middle
throughout the entire process.

00:04:15.246 --> 00:04:16.505 A:middle
The first one is the most

00:04:16.505 --> 00:04:17.625 A:middle
straightforward, so let's just

00:04:17.796 --> 00:04:19.696 A:middle
jump right into that one, and

00:04:19.696 --> 00:04:20.976 A:middle
that is that dark interfaces are

00:04:20.976 --> 00:04:23.716 A:middle
cool, period, right?

00:04:23.976 --> 00:04:25.386 A:middle
They are almost effortlessly

00:04:25.386 --> 00:04:26.736 A:middle
cool in a way that light

00:04:26.736 --> 00:04:28.116 A:middle
interfaces sometimes kind of

00:04:28.176 --> 00:04:28.976 A:middle
struggle to be.

00:04:29.456 --> 00:04:31.006 A:middle
But why is that, really?

00:04:31.386 --> 00:04:32.926 A:middle
Part of it is because we all

00:04:32.926 --> 00:04:34.206 A:middle
have these notions of what a

00:04:34.206 --> 00:04:35.706 A:middle
dark interface is and what a

00:04:35.706 --> 00:04:36.876 A:middle
dark interface looks like.

00:04:37.246 --> 00:04:38.646 A:middle
And a lot of that is fed into us

00:04:38.716 --> 00:04:39.876 A:middle
by what we've seen in pop

00:04:39.876 --> 00:04:41.286 A:middle
cultures in things such as

00:04:41.776 --> 00:04:43.626 A:middle
sci-fi movies and action movies.

00:04:44.216 --> 00:04:45.456 A:middle
So much so that if I were to go

00:04:45.456 --> 00:04:46.476 A:middle
around the audience and ask

00:04:46.476 --> 00:04:47.716 A:middle
everyone to give me one-word

00:04:47.716 --> 00:04:49.476 A:middle
association of what a dark

00:04:49.476 --> 00:04:51.236 A:middle
interface is to them, I'd get

00:04:51.236 --> 00:04:52.516 A:middle
responses such as cool, of

00:04:52.576 --> 00:04:55.596 A:middle
course; slick; professional;

00:04:56.056 --> 00:04:58.276 A:middle
futuristic; and even beautiful.

00:04:59.576 --> 00:05:01.786 A:middle
So going into the design for


00:04:59.576 --> 00:05:01.786 A:middle
So going into the design for

00:05:01.786 --> 00:05:03.406 A:middle
Dark Mode, we really wanted to

00:05:03.406 --> 00:05:04.346 A:middle
acknowledge all of these

00:05:04.346 --> 00:05:06.246 A:middle
aesthetic associations that we

00:05:06.246 --> 00:05:08.306 A:middle
all have with dark interfaces,

00:05:08.766 --> 00:05:10.986 A:middle
while at the same time embracing

00:05:10.986 --> 00:05:12.536 A:middle
a lot of the real benefits that

00:05:12.536 --> 00:05:14.496 A:middle
a dark design offers you, such

00:05:14.496 --> 00:05:16.256 A:middle
as a higher contrast for

00:05:17.706 --> 00:05:18.136 A:middle
typography.

00:05:18.136 --> 00:05:20.426 A:middle
We realize that Dark Mode is

00:05:20.486 --> 00:05:22.176 A:middle
really, really cool, and that a

00:05:22.176 --> 00:05:23.216 A:middle
lot of you are going to want to

00:05:23.216 --> 00:05:24.656 A:middle
adopt Dark Mode on your apps

00:05:24.776 --> 00:05:25.436 A:middle
permanently.

00:05:25.576 --> 00:05:27.666 A:middle
But, in actuality, only a small

00:05:27.736 --> 00:05:29.016 A:middle
subset of apps really should be

00:05:29.016 --> 00:05:31.666 A:middle
dark all the time, and those are

00:05:31.666 --> 00:05:33.646 A:middle
things that are media-centric or

00:05:33.646 --> 00:05:34.856 A:middle
content-creation apps.

00:05:34.926 --> 00:05:35.886 A:middle
Those are the ones that are best

00:05:35.926 --> 00:05:37.246 A:middle
suited to staying dark all the

00:05:37.246 --> 00:05:38.766 A:middle
time, so if your app doesn't

00:05:38.766 --> 00:05:39.516 A:middle
fall into one of those

00:05:39.516 --> 00:05:41.366 A:middle
categories, it's better to let

00:05:41.366 --> 00:05:42.686 A:middle
your app follow what the system

00:05:42.686 --> 00:05:43.876 A:middle
appearance is, rather than to

00:05:43.876 --> 00:05:45.046 A:middle
make it dark permanently.

00:05:45.046 --> 00:05:49.606 A:middle
The second principle was that

00:05:49.816 --> 00:05:51.576 A:middle
dark interfaces are not just

00:05:51.576 --> 00:05:52.146 A:middle
inverted.

00:05:52.486 --> 00:05:53.886 A:middle
And, really, what's at the core

00:05:53.976 --> 00:05:56.356 A:middle
here is that when you look at a

00:05:56.356 --> 00:05:57.946 A:middle
dark interface, it can sometimes

00:05:57.996 --> 00:06:00.416 A:middle
be easy to think of just taking


00:05:57.996 --> 00:06:00.416 A:middle
be easy to think of just taking

00:06:00.416 --> 00:06:01.486 A:middle
the light interface and

00:06:01.486 --> 00:06:02.826 A:middle
inverting it to end up with your

00:06:02.826 --> 00:06:03.666 A:middle
final result.

00:06:04.186 --> 00:06:05.946 A:middle
But, in actuality, that can be

00:06:05.946 --> 00:06:07.986 A:middle
very creatively limiting, and so

00:06:07.986 --> 00:06:09.526 A:middle
it's better to take a look at

00:06:09.526 --> 00:06:10.276 A:middle
your elements and your

00:06:10.276 --> 00:06:12.186 A:middle
application on a case-by-case

00:06:12.716 --> 00:06:16.006 A:middle
basis and try to determine what

00:06:16.006 --> 00:06:18.316 A:middle
is the visual cue that they're

00:06:18.316 --> 00:06:19.826 A:middle
trying to communicate and then

00:06:19.826 --> 00:06:21.926 A:middle
figure out whether an opposite

00:06:21.926 --> 00:06:23.406 A:middle
visual cue is necessary.

00:06:24.286 --> 00:06:25.136 A:middle
So, if you take something, for

00:06:25.136 --> 00:06:27.376 A:middle
example, like, a standard Light

00:06:27.476 --> 00:06:28.706 A:middle
push button in the light

00:06:28.706 --> 00:06:30.376 A:middle
appearance, the buttons look

00:06:30.376 --> 00:06:31.756 A:middle
like this in their active state.

00:06:32.346 --> 00:06:33.656 A:middle
And, then, when you click on

00:06:33.656 --> 00:06:35.026 A:middle
them, the buttons darken.

00:06:35.236 --> 00:06:37.046 A:middle
And this is generally true of

00:06:37.386 --> 00:06:38.546 A:middle
almost all of the controls in

00:06:38.546 --> 00:06:39.636 A:middle
the light appearance in that

00:06:39.686 --> 00:06:41.336 A:middle
their click state is a darker

00:06:41.336 --> 00:06:42.486 A:middle
version of what their active

00:06:42.576 --> 00:06:43.056 A:middle
state was.

00:06:44.266 --> 00:06:45.716 A:middle
In Dark Mode, however, the

00:06:45.746 --> 00:06:47.096 A:middle
general active state looks like

00:06:47.096 --> 00:06:48.996 A:middle
this, and when you click on

00:06:48.996 --> 00:06:50.486 A:middle
them, they brighten, and that,

00:06:50.486 --> 00:06:52.096 A:middle
again, is generally true of all

00:06:52.096 --> 00:06:52.866 A:middle
of the controls.

00:06:52.866 --> 00:06:54.546 A:middle
They will all generally brighten

00:06:56.496 --> 00:06:56.746 A:middle
up.

00:06:56.746 --> 00:06:59.446 A:middle
Another example are group boxes.


00:07:00.066 --> 00:07:01.126 A:middle
In light appearance, the group

00:07:01.126 --> 00:07:02.966 A:middle
boxes have a dark fill behind

00:07:02.966 --> 00:07:05.756 A:middle
them and are shaded such along

00:07:05.756 --> 00:07:07.586 A:middle
the edges to give them a

00:07:07.586 --> 00:07:09.216 A:middle
recessed quality such that they

00:07:09.216 --> 00:07:10.346 A:middle
look like they're carved into

00:07:10.346 --> 00:07:11.286 A:middle
the window background that

00:07:11.286 --> 00:07:12.436 A:middle
they're inside of.

00:07:13.696 --> 00:07:16.166 A:middle
In Dark Mode, however, the group

00:07:16.166 --> 00:07:17.586 A:middle
boxes are treated almost as if

00:07:17.586 --> 00:07:19.176 A:middle
they are self-illuminated.

00:07:19.746 --> 00:07:22.156 A:middle
But, at the end of the day, the

00:07:22.236 --> 00:07:23.856 A:middle
general purpose of the group box

00:07:23.856 --> 00:07:24.916 A:middle
is the same between the two

00:07:24.916 --> 00:07:27.016 A:middle
modes in that what they're

00:07:27.016 --> 00:07:28.066 A:middle
really trying to communicate to

00:07:28.066 --> 00:07:29.526 A:middle
the user is that the contents

00:07:29.576 --> 00:07:31.406 A:middle
contained therein are all

00:07:31.406 --> 00:07:32.316 A:middle
related somehow.

00:07:34.026 --> 00:07:35.956 A:middle
Why I said that it was important

00:07:36.026 --> 00:07:38.166 A:middle
to go on a case-by-case basis

00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:39.976 A:middle
and try and determine what the

00:07:39.976 --> 00:07:43.176 A:middle
visual cue that your elements

00:07:43.486 --> 00:07:45.266 A:middle
are trying to communicate-- It's

00:07:45.266 --> 00:07:46.916 A:middle
important, is because, in some

00:07:46.916 --> 00:07:48.306 A:middle
cases, the visual cue that's

00:07:48.376 --> 00:07:50.206 A:middle
being communicated is already

00:07:50.206 --> 00:07:51.506 A:middle
effective enough in the Light

00:07:51.506 --> 00:07:53.376 A:middle
Mode and should be left as is in

00:07:53.376 --> 00:07:53.916 A:middle
Dark Mode.

00:07:54.486 --> 00:07:56.086 A:middle
An example of this are the

00:07:56.086 --> 00:07:56.906 A:middle
window shadows.

00:07:57.786 --> 00:08:00.596 A:middle
As we all know, macOS is a


00:07:57.786 --> 00:08:00.596 A:middle
As we all know, macOS is a

00:08:00.596 --> 00:08:02.786 A:middle
layered window environment, and

00:08:02.786 --> 00:08:03.946 A:middle
the window shadows really help

00:08:03.946 --> 00:08:04.946 A:middle
to communicate the sense of

00:08:05.006 --> 00:08:06.236 A:middle
depth, the Z-depth of the

00:08:06.236 --> 00:08:06.766 A:middle
windows.

00:08:07.396 --> 00:08:08.686 A:middle
So, if we were to have inverted

00:08:08.686 --> 00:08:10.056 A:middle
the window shadows, for example,

00:08:10.056 --> 00:08:11.406 A:middle
and started using a white

00:08:11.406 --> 00:08:13.246 A:middle
shadow, for example, the entire

00:08:13.246 --> 00:08:14.606 A:middle
UI would have become flat.

00:08:14.756 --> 00:08:15.796 A:middle
You would have lost that sense

00:08:17.756 --> 00:08:19.186 A:middle
of depth.

00:08:19.186 --> 00:08:20.256 A:middle
Another thing to note is that

00:08:20.256 --> 00:08:21.836 A:middle
the window shadows in macOS are

00:08:21.836 --> 00:08:23.206 A:middle
constructed of two layers.

00:08:23.286 --> 00:08:24.666 A:middle
We've got the diffused shadow

00:08:24.766 --> 00:08:25.546 A:middle
and the rim shadow.

00:08:25.986 --> 00:08:27.536 A:middle
So, if we look at this little

00:08:27.536 --> 00:08:30.626 A:middle
portion of the screen and look

00:08:30.626 --> 00:08:31.256 A:middle
at how the shadows were

00:08:31.256 --> 00:08:33.126 A:middle
constructed and treated in Dark

00:08:33.126 --> 00:08:35.166 A:middle
Mode, the first thing to note is

00:08:35.246 --> 00:08:36.775 A:middle
that, in taking into

00:08:36.775 --> 00:08:38.895 A:middle
consideration that users are

00:08:39.196 --> 00:08:40.775 A:middle
going to be able to go back and

00:08:40.775 --> 00:08:42.086 A:middle
forth between light and dark

00:08:42.086 --> 00:08:44.536 A:middle
appearance quite often and that

