some apps are going to stay dark

00:08:46.246 --> 00:08:47.766 A:middle
all the time, it was important

00:08:47.806 --> 00:08:48.996 A:middle
for us to keep the diffused

00:08:48.996 --> 00:08:50.896 A:middle
shadow exactly the same.

00:08:51.546 --> 00:08:53.706 A:middle
So, we used the exact same

00:08:53.706 --> 00:08:55.406 A:middle
shadow blur parameters for the

00:08:55.406 --> 00:08:56.796 A:middle
shadows in Dark Mode.

00:08:57.786 --> 00:08:59.536 A:middle
Next, we took a look at the rim

00:08:59.536 --> 00:09:02.426 A:middle
shadows and saw what changes we


00:08:59.536 --> 00:09:02.426 A:middle
shadows and saw what changes we

00:09:02.426 --> 00:09:04.066 A:middle
needed to do for those, and the

00:09:04.066 --> 00:09:05.176 A:middle
changes that we did for Dark

00:09:05.236 --> 00:09:06.696 A:middle
Mode where we adjusted the

00:09:06.696 --> 00:09:07.826 A:middle
opacity to make them a little

00:09:07.826 --> 00:09:09.816 A:middle
bit higher so that the contrast

00:09:09.856 --> 00:09:12.086 A:middle
edge was more defined and that

00:09:12.086 --> 00:09:13.236 A:middle
we made them a little bit

00:09:13.306 --> 00:09:13.676 A:middle
crisper.

00:09:14.336 --> 00:09:18.866 A:middle
To further the focus and the

00:09:18.866 --> 00:09:20.886 A:middle
edge detail on the windows, we

00:09:20.886 --> 00:09:24.026 A:middle
added an inner rim stroke to the

00:09:24.026 --> 00:09:26.476 A:middle
windows to really help define

00:09:26.476 --> 00:09:28.646 A:middle
the windows and pop them off.

00:09:29.186 --> 00:09:30.306 A:middle
The end result is that the

00:09:30.306 --> 00:09:32.606 A:middle
visual cue still looks very

00:09:32.606 --> 00:09:34.406 A:middle
similar to the light appearance,

00:09:34.686 --> 00:09:37.366 A:middle
but the end result has been

00:09:37.366 --> 00:09:39.196 A:middle
finely tuned for dark appearance

00:09:39.196 --> 00:09:40.906 A:middle
so that it works much better.

00:09:46.046 --> 00:09:47.926 A:middle
The second principle was that

00:09:47.926 --> 00:09:49.276 A:middle
Dark Mode is content focused,

00:09:49.276 --> 00:09:50.166 A:middle
and this was the one that we

00:09:50.166 --> 00:09:51.676 A:middle
referred back to the most often

00:09:51.676 --> 00:09:52.826 A:middle
throughout the entire process,

00:09:52.826 --> 00:09:53.246 A:middle
actually.

00:09:54.246 --> 00:09:56.896 A:middle
When you look at a light

00:09:56.896 --> 00:09:58.066 A:middle
interface screen, it can

00:09:58.066 --> 00:09:59.226 A:middle
sometimes be a little difficult

00:09:59.226 --> 00:10:01.396 A:middle
to tell what the content is,


00:09:59.226 --> 00:10:01.396 A:middle
to tell what the content is,

00:10:01.566 --> 00:10:03.366 A:middle
where to focus your attention

00:10:03.366 --> 00:10:04.606 A:middle
to, especially when there are

00:10:04.606 --> 00:10:06.286 A:middle
lots of windows on the screen.

00:10:07.156 --> 00:10:08.386 A:middle
And part of the reason for that

00:10:08.386 --> 00:10:09.956 A:middle
is because a lot of the content

00:10:10.006 --> 00:10:11.186 A:middle
that we all create is just

00:10:11.256 --> 00:10:12.456 A:middle
bright in general.

00:10:13.146 --> 00:10:16.336 A:middle
However, in a dark UI, the

00:10:16.336 --> 00:10:18.326 A:middle
content stands out because of

00:10:18.366 --> 00:10:20.206 A:middle
the background being pretty

00:10:20.986 --> 00:10:21.246 A:middle
dark.

00:10:21.246 --> 00:10:22.676 A:middle
All of the window chrome in the

00:10:22.676 --> 00:10:24.756 A:middle
background generally just melts

00:10:24.756 --> 00:10:26.466 A:middle
away, and the content becomes

00:10:26.466 --> 00:10:27.646 A:middle
the primary focus of your

00:10:27.646 --> 00:10:28.136 A:middle
attention.

00:10:29.296 --> 00:10:30.246 A:middle
Generally, we found that there

00:10:30.246 --> 00:10:32.096 A:middle
were three methods for how to

00:10:32.226 --> 00:10:33.996 A:middle
treat your content regions

00:10:33.996 --> 00:10:35.656 A:middle
inside of your windows to

00:10:35.656 --> 00:10:37.406 A:middle
optimize the content focus.

00:10:38.596 --> 00:10:39.926 A:middle
The first method was to just

00:10:40.066 --> 00:10:42.466 A:middle
generally go completely dark.

00:10:42.636 --> 00:10:43.946 A:middle
An app like Finder is a great

00:10:43.946 --> 00:10:45.076 A:middle
example of where this is

00:10:45.136 --> 00:10:47.246 A:middle
possible because of the way that

00:10:47.246 --> 00:10:48.396 A:middle
the content is displayed.

00:10:48.936 --> 00:10:50.646 A:middle
Finder's content are displayed

00:10:50.646 --> 00:10:53.316 A:middle
as colorful file icons and so

00:10:53.316 --> 00:10:54.516 A:middle
the dark background really helps

00:10:54.606 --> 00:10:56.606 A:middle
the icons stand out as much as

00:10:58.106 --> 00:10:58.536 A:middle
possible.

00:10:58.536 --> 00:11:00.626 A:middle
The second method was to leave


00:10:58.536 --> 00:11:00.626 A:middle
The second method was to leave

00:11:00.736 --> 00:11:02.716 A:middle
the content as is.

00:11:03.226 --> 00:11:04.826 A:middle
Pages is a great example of what

00:11:04.826 --> 00:11:06.726 A:middle
you see is what you get app,

00:11:06.916 --> 00:11:08.036 A:middle
where the contents should be

00:11:08.036 --> 00:11:09.646 A:middle
rendered and presented exactly

00:11:09.646 --> 00:11:12.776 A:middle
as the user authored and created

00:11:12.776 --> 00:11:12.946 A:middle
it.

00:11:13.826 --> 00:11:16.276 A:middle
Dark Mode is a great UI for what

00:11:16.646 --> 00:11:17.856 A:middle
you see is what you get apps,

00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:19.566 A:middle
because the content really

00:11:19.566 --> 00:11:21.906 A:middle
becomes the primary focus, and

00:11:21.906 --> 00:11:23.576 A:middle
the UI really becomes the

00:11:23.636 --> 00:11:25.136 A:middle
secondary focus and almost melts

00:11:25.136 --> 00:11:25.536 A:middle
away.

00:11:27.486 --> 00:11:32.846 A:middle
The third method was to make the

00:11:32.846 --> 00:11:34.696 A:middle
content region appearance a user

00:11:34.696 --> 00:11:35.246 A:middle
option.

00:11:35.956 --> 00:11:37.456 A:middle
Mail is a good example of an app

00:11:37.456 --> 00:11:38.616 A:middle
where the appearance of the

00:11:38.686 --> 00:11:40.786 A:middle
content might be ambiguous as to

00:11:40.786 --> 00:11:41.946 A:middle
whether the user would prefer it

00:11:41.986 --> 00:11:44.386 A:middle
to be light or dark, and so the

00:11:44.386 --> 00:11:46.486 A:middle
best thing to do is to make an

00:11:46.486 --> 00:11:47.796 A:middle
application setting so that the

00:11:47.796 --> 00:11:49.066 A:middle
user can determine whether they

00:11:49.066 --> 00:11:50.276 A:middle
want it to be light or dark on

00:11:50.276 --> 00:11:51.406 A:middle
their own, while their

00:11:51.406 --> 00:11:53.806 A:middle
application's chrome area still

00:11:53.806 --> 00:11:55.416 A:middle
respects the overall system

00:11:58.346 --> 00:11:58.806 A:middle
appearance.

00:11:59.226 --> 00:12:00.216 A:middle
One thing that all three of


00:11:59.226 --> 00:12:00.216 A:middle
One thing that all three of

00:12:00.216 --> 00:12:01.866 A:middle
these windows had in common was

00:12:01.936 --> 00:12:03.796 A:middle
that the chrome remained dark

00:12:04.206 --> 00:12:06.096 A:middle
and became secondary to the

00:12:06.096 --> 00:12:06.826 A:middle
content area.

00:12:06.826 --> 00:12:09.026 A:middle
And Dark Mode kind of achieves

00:12:09.096 --> 00:12:10.666 A:middle
this using a feature that we

00:12:10.666 --> 00:12:11.946 A:middle
call desktop tinting, which

00:12:12.336 --> 00:12:14.586 A:middle
causes the window's background

00:12:14.586 --> 00:12:16.576 A:middle
colors to camouflage themselves

00:12:16.926 --> 00:12:17.966 A:middle
with the desktop picture.

00:12:17.966 --> 00:12:20.286 A:middle
We found that completely

00:12:20.286 --> 00:12:22.386 A:middle
desaturated gray colors have a

00:12:22.386 --> 00:12:23.606 A:middle
tendency to have a color

00:12:23.606 --> 00:12:25.226 A:middle
temperature that was sometimes

00:12:25.226 --> 00:12:26.336 A:middle
in conflict with what your

00:12:26.596 --> 00:12:28.596 A:middle
desktop picture was, and this

00:12:28.596 --> 00:12:30.496 A:middle
effect was magnified when you

00:12:30.496 --> 00:12:32.646 A:middle
have a translucent sidebar area,

00:12:32.646 --> 00:12:35.696 A:middle
for example, against a solid

00:12:35.696 --> 00:12:38.526 A:middle
opaque area of your window, and

00:12:38.526 --> 00:12:39.626 A:middle
so desktop tinting helps

00:12:39.686 --> 00:12:40.416 A:middle
mitigate that.

00:12:40.886 --> 00:12:41.986 A:middle
Once applied, the desktop

00:12:42.046 --> 00:12:43.656 A:middle
tinting gives the whole window a

00:12:43.656 --> 00:12:45.346 A:middle
harmonious color scheme, which

00:12:45.526 --> 00:12:48.716 A:middle
helps it to blend in with the

00:12:48.756 --> 00:12:50.916 A:middle
surrounding areas and really

00:12:50.916 --> 00:12:52.236 A:middle
reduces that color temperature

00:12:52.236 --> 00:12:52.906 A:middle
disparity.

00:12:54.506 --> 00:12:56.616 A:middle
So, how do we do the desktop

00:12:56.656 --> 00:12:57.776 A:middle
tinting effect?

00:12:57.896 --> 00:12:58.916 A:middle
The first thing that we do is,

00:12:58.916 --> 00:13:00.946 A:middle
actually, we take a sample of


00:12:58.916 --> 00:13:00.946 A:middle
actually, we take a sample of

00:13:00.946 --> 00:13:01.936 A:middle
the desktop portion that is

00:13:01.976 --> 00:13:04.626 A:middle
behind the window, and then we

00:13:04.686 --> 00:13:07.416 A:middle
derive a average color for that

00:13:07.416 --> 00:13:09.656 A:middle
area, and then we blend that

00:13:09.656 --> 00:13:12.426 A:middle
average color with a gray, which

00:13:12.496 --> 00:13:13.566 A:middle
then becomes the window

00:13:13.566 --> 00:13:14.346 A:middle
background color.

00:13:15.326 --> 00:13:16.406 A:middle
This background color is

00:13:16.406 --> 00:13:18.366 A:middle
dynamic, so as the user moves

00:13:18.366 --> 00:13:19.596 A:middle
the window around the screen,

00:13:19.596 --> 00:13:21.186 A:middle
the color will update itself so

00:13:21.186 --> 00:13:22.456 A:middle
that the window always stays in

00:13:22.456 --> 00:13:24.326 A:middle
sync with the wallpaper portion

00:13:24.326 --> 00:13:25.176 A:middle
that was behind it.

00:13:25.706 --> 00:13:28.566 A:middle
So, if we look at the effect in

00:13:28.566 --> 00:13:29.746 A:middle
action across a couple of

00:13:29.746 --> 00:13:31.656 A:middle
different wallpapers, you can

00:13:31.656 --> 00:13:32.916 A:middle
see that the window is adjusting

00:13:32.916 --> 00:13:34.676 A:middle
itself on the right side to

00:13:34.676 --> 00:13:37.196 A:middle
match the desktop picture that

00:13:37.196 --> 00:13:37.816 A:middle
is behind it.

00:13:39.166 --> 00:13:41.196 A:middle
Not only does the window

00:13:41.196 --> 00:13:44.106 A:middle
background color adjust itself

00:13:44.106 --> 00:13:45.526 A:middle
to take advantage of the desktop

00:13:45.666 --> 00:13:47.566 A:middle
color, but the controls also get

00:13:47.566 --> 00:13:48.666 A:middle
a little bit of that going

00:13:48.666 --> 00:13:49.986 A:middle
through them also due to the

00:13:49.986 --> 00:13:51.146 A:middle
control's opacity.

00:13:53.396 --> 00:13:56.696 A:middle
For users that work in

00:13:56.696 --> 00:13:58.756 A:middle
color-sensitive applications or

00:13:58.756 --> 00:14:00.456 A:middle
have very color-sensitive


00:13:58.756 --> 00:14:00.456 A:middle
have very color-sensitive

00:14:00.796 --> 00:14:02.456 A:middle
content or just generally would

00:14:02.456 --> 00:14:03.776 A:middle
prefer not to have the desktop

00:14:03.776 --> 00:14:07.996 A:middle
tinting apply to their UI, we

00:14:07.996 --> 00:14:09.986 A:middle
offer the Graphite Mode so that

00:14:09.986 --> 00:14:11.466 A:middle
they can disable the color

00:14:11.536 --> 00:14:15.106 A:middle
tinting altogether.

00:14:15.106 --> 00:14:16.946 A:middle
If we take a look at the color

00:14:16.946 --> 00:14:18.106 A:middle
swatches for the window

00:14:18.106 --> 00:14:20.306 A:middle
background colors, along the top

00:14:20.306 --> 00:14:21.546 A:middle
there, we can see the window

00:14:21.546 --> 00:14:23.406 A:middle
background color in the Light

00:14:23.436 --> 00:14:25.586 A:middle
Mode, which is the standard

00:14:25.646 --> 00:14:26.546 A:middle
light gray that we're all

00:14:26.606 --> 00:14:27.416 A:middle
accustomed to.

00:14:27.736 --> 00:14:28.746 A:middle
And, in the middle there, we've

00:14:28.786 --> 00:14:30.126 A:middle
got the under page background

00:14:30.126 --> 00:14:31.876 A:middle
color, which is a mid-tone gray,

00:14:32.376 --> 00:14:34.196 A:middle
and then we've got the content

00:14:34.196 --> 00:14:35.836 A:middle
background, which is the white

00:14:35.936 --> 00:14:36.936 A:middle
background color that we're all

00:14:36.936 --> 00:14:38.976 A:middle
familiar with behind all of our

00:14:38.976 --> 00:14:39.806 A:middle
content areas.

00:14:40.716 --> 00:14:42.016 A:middle
In the middle row, you can see

00:14:42.016 --> 00:14:43.876 A:middle
how the desktop tinting affects

00:14:43.986 --> 00:14:45.636 A:middle
these colors, and, then, along

00:14:45.636 --> 00:14:46.896 A:middle
the bottom, you can see the

00:14:46.896 --> 00:14:48.476 A:middle
effects of the graphite accent

00:14:48.546 --> 00:14:50.456 A:middle
color disabling the desktop

00:14:50.516 --> 00:14:51.146 A:middle
tinting effect.

00:14:54.566 --> 00:14:55.636 A:middle
So, now that we've gone over

00:14:55.636 --> 00:14:56.866 A:middle
some of the design principles,

00:14:57.036 --> 00:14:58.276 A:middle
let's go into a little bit of

00:14:58.276 --> 00:14:59.426 A:middle
the design considerations that

00:14:59.426 --> 00:15:00.506 A:middle
you should take into account


00:14:59.426 --> 00:15:00.506 A:middle
you should take into account

00:15:00.506 --> 00:15:03.316 A:middle
when updating your apps.

00:15:03.316 --> 00:15:04.416 A:middle
First, let's talk about colors.

00:15:06.186 --> 00:15:08.746 A:middle
For macOS 10.14, we added a lot

00:15:08.746 --> 00:15:09.286 A:middle
of colors.

00:15:09.926 --> 00:15:12.056 A:middle
We also removed a lot of colors,

00:15:12.246 --> 00:15:15.446 A:middle
updated some, and, as you can

00:15:15.446 --> 00:15:16.706 A:middle
see behind me, these are some of

00:15:16.706 --> 00:15:17.616 A:middle
our system colors.

00:15:17.826 --> 00:15:19.696 A:middle
Along the bottom, we've got the

00:15:19.696 --> 00:15:21.026 A:middle
dark variance of the colors,

00:15:21.456 --> 00:15:23.506 A:middle
and, as you can see, the dark

00:15:23.506 --> 00:15:24.916 A:middle
versions are generally a little

00:15:24.916 --> 00:15:26.626 A:middle
bit brighter and more saturated.

00:15:27.636 --> 00:15:29.356 A:middle
Rachel and Taylor are going to a

00:15:29.356 --> 00:15:30.636 A:middle
little bit deeper into the color

00:15:30.846 --> 00:15:32.266 A:middle
usage during their portion of

00:15:32.316 --> 00:15:34.136 A:middle
today's session, but, for now, I

00:15:34.166 --> 00:15:35.656 A:middle
just generally want to try and

00:15:35.656 --> 00:15:36.566 A:middle
cover three colors in

00:15:36.566 --> 00:15:38.356 A:middle
particular, which are the blues.

00:15:39.476 --> 00:15:41.086 A:middle
Going from left to right, we've

00:15:41.126 --> 00:15:42.336 A:middle
got controlAccentColor,

00:15:42.766 --> 00:15:44.456 A:middle
systemBlueColor, and linkColor.

00:15:45.146 --> 00:15:47.076 A:middle
Linkcolor, as the name implies,

00:15:47.536 --> 00:15:49.936 A:middle
is meant to be applied to links,

00:15:50.066 --> 00:15:51.156 A:middle
text links in particular.

00:15:51.616 --> 00:15:53.536 A:middle
So, things that are hyperlinks,

00:15:53.956 --> 00:15:55.576 A:middle
taking of the user to a website,

00:15:55.656 --> 00:15:57.456 A:middle
or a link within your

00:15:57.456 --> 00:15:58.846 A:middle
application that navigates the

00:15:58.846 --> 00:16:00.336 A:middle
user to another area of your


00:15:58.846 --> 00:16:00.336 A:middle
user to another area of your

00:16:00.336 --> 00:16:01.566 A:middle
application-- those should be

00:16:01.566 --> 00:16:02.526 A:middle
treated with linkColor.

00:16:03.476 --> 00:16:04.816 A:middle
ControlAccentColor and

00:16:04.816 --> 00:16:06.696 A:middle
systemBlueColor are really meant

00:16:06.696 --> 00:16:09.136 A:middle
to be used on controls that have

00:16:09.196 --> 00:16:10.896 A:middle
visible borders or button bezel

00:16:10.896 --> 00:16:13.496 A:middle
backgrounds or for tinted

00:16:13.546 --> 00:16:13.856 A:middle
glyphs.

00:16:15.086 --> 00:16:16.516 A:middle
ControlAccentColor, as the name

00:16:16.556 --> 00:16:19.416 A:middle
implies, is going to respond to

00:16:19.486 --> 00:16:21.296 A:middle
whatever the system accent color

00:16:21.296 --> 00:16:22.866 A:middle
is set to, in this case, red.

00:16:23.556 --> 00:16:25.026 A:middle
So, if you have a custom control

00:16:25.026 --> 00:16:26.186 A:middle
that is trying to mimic the

00:16:26.186 --> 00:16:28.086 A:middle
appearance of a standard system

00:16:28.086 --> 00:16:29.886 A:middle
control, or you just have a

00:16:29.886 --> 00:16:31.196 A:middle
control that you would like to

00:16:31.296 --> 00:16:32.476 A:middle
follow suit with whatever the

00:16:32.516 --> 00:16:34.486 A:middle
system appearance is set to, you

00:16:34.486 --> 00:16:35.896 A:middle
should use controlAccentColor.

00:16:36.526 --> 00:16:38.036 A:middle
If you have a control where it's

00:16:38.036 --> 00:16:39.386 A:middle
important that the control stays

00:16:39.386 --> 00:16:41.646 A:middle
blue because of informational

00:16:41.646 --> 00:16:43.076 A:middle
purposes or for branding

00:16:43.076 --> 00:16:45.506 A:middle
purposes, then systemBlueColor

00:16:45.506 --> 00:16:46.516 A:middle
is a better choice for you to

00:16:46.516 --> 00:16:46.846 A:middle
use.

00:16:48.826 --> 00:16:50.286 A:middle
Next, let's take a look at

00:16:50.286 --> 00:16:51.336 A:middle
designing with vibrancy.

00:16:53.196 --> 00:16:54.926 A:middle
When we talk about vibrancy,

00:16:54.926 --> 00:16:56.036 A:middle
what we're generally referring

00:16:56.036 --> 00:16:58.066 A:middle
to is the package of a

00:16:58.066 --> 00:17:00.356 A:middle
translucent material working in


00:16:58.066 --> 00:17:00.356 A:middle
translucent material working in

00:17:00.356 --> 00:17:01.526 A:middle
conjunction with the content

00:17:01.526 --> 00:17:02.676 A:middle
that is displayed above it.

00:17:03.226 --> 00:17:05.626 A:middle
So, in this case, the vibrancy

00:17:05.705 --> 00:17:07.955 A:middle
is the vibrant Finder sidebar.

00:17:10.076 --> 00:17:12.296 A:middle
Generally, we have non-colored

00:17:12.726 --> 00:17:14.965 A:middle
artwork that is meant to be

00:17:14.965 --> 00:17:16.076 A:middle
treated vibrantly.

00:17:16.076 --> 00:17:19.195 A:middle
An example of that is the glyphs

00:17:19.356 --> 00:17:21.606 A:middle
and the text in the Finder

00:17:21.606 --> 00:17:23.175 A:middle
sidebar here.

00:17:23.616 --> 00:17:25.756 A:middle
The end result of the vibrancy

00:17:25.756 --> 00:17:28.056 A:middle
is is that the colors become

00:17:28.136 --> 00:17:30.196 A:middle
higher saturation, and the

00:17:30.356 --> 00:17:31.946 A:middle
contrast is increased for things

00:17:31.946 --> 00:17:32.456 A:middle
like the text.

00:17:33.856 --> 00:17:35.616 A:middle
Colored artwork, such as the

00:17:35.616 --> 00:17:37.416 A:middle
finder tags in this example,

00:17:37.776 --> 00:17:38.506 A:middle
should be treated as

00:17:38.506 --> 00:17:40.196 A:middle
non-vibrant.

00:17:40.346 --> 00:17:41.636 A:middle
Same thing with colored

00:17:41.636 --> 00:17:42.406 A:middle
iconography.

00:17:42.816 --> 00:17:45.246 A:middle
The vibrancy will destroy the

00:17:45.246 --> 00:17:46.836 A:middle
original colors that you have in

00:17:46.836 --> 00:17:48.456 A:middle
your image, and so you want to

00:17:48.456 --> 00:17:49.646 A:middle
treat those as non-vibrant.

00:17:50.416 --> 00:17:52.756 A:middle
So, taking a look at how you can

00:17:52.756 --> 00:17:55.806 A:middle
construct vibrant content, it

00:17:55.806 --> 00:17:57.946 A:middle
might seem almost obvious to

00:17:57.946 --> 00:18:00.466 A:middle
just use opacities, in this


00:17:57.946 --> 00:18:00.466 A:middle
just use opacities, in this

00:18:00.556 --> 00:18:02.726 A:middle
case, opacities of white.

00:18:03.316 --> 00:18:05.276 A:middle
But while it's true that some

00:18:05.276 --> 00:18:06.636 A:middle
color contribution from the

00:18:06.636 --> 00:18:08.156 A:middle
background is occurring through

00:18:08.156 --> 00:18:12.206 A:middle
the materials here-- and that's

00:18:12.206 --> 00:18:12.946 A:middle
happening because of the

00:18:12.946 --> 00:18:14.456 A:middle
opacity-- the end result is

00:18:14.456 --> 00:18:16.346 A:middle
actually not as highly saturated

00:18:16.346 --> 00:18:17.336 A:middle
as we would desire.

00:18:17.446 --> 00:18:19.546 A:middle
And, as you can see along the

00:18:20.026 --> 00:18:22.946 A:middle
bottom with the Quaternary Label

00:18:22.946 --> 00:18:25.396 A:middle
Color, the legibility is a

00:18:25.396 --> 00:18:26.446 A:middle
little bit compromised.

00:18:27.696 --> 00:18:29.216 A:middle
Instead, what you want to do is

00:18:29.266 --> 00:18:30.576 A:middle
construct these using opaque

00:18:30.756 --> 00:18:31.636 A:middle
grayscale colors.

00:18:32.416 --> 00:18:34.786 A:middle
One thing to note here is that

00:18:34.886 --> 00:18:37.266 A:middle
the text color for the RGB label

00:18:37.266 --> 00:18:39.756 A:middle
colors here are full black.

00:18:40.336 --> 00:18:42.726 A:middle
What's going to happen once the

00:18:42.726 --> 00:18:44.146 A:middle
Blend Mode is applied is that

00:18:44.216 --> 00:18:46.406 A:middle
the text that is black is going

00:18:46.556 --> 00:18:47.806 A:middle
to become completely

00:18:47.806 --> 00:18:48.466 A:middle
transparent.

00:18:48.916 --> 00:18:50.046 A:middle
So, if you have areas of your

00:18:50.046 --> 00:18:51.316 A:middle
content that need to be treated

00:18:51.316 --> 00:18:53.236 A:middle
as a knockout, use full opaque

00:18:53.326 --> 00:18:54.956 A:middle
black, and if you have areas

00:18:54.956 --> 00:18:56.626 A:middle
that need to be gradiate towards

00:18:56.896 --> 00:18:59.226 A:middle
an opacity, use a gray that is

00:18:59.456 --> 00:19:00.706 A:middle
ramping itself towards a full


00:18:59.456 --> 00:19:00.706 A:middle
ramping itself towards a full

00:19:00.706 --> 00:19:00.916 A:middle
black.

00:19:01.656 --> 00:19:03.186 A:middle
This is true in Dark Mode, and

00:19:03.186 --> 00:19:04.506 A:middle
the opposite is true in Light

00:19:04.546 --> 00:19:05.986 A:middle
Mode, in light, vibrant areas, I

00:19:05.986 --> 00:19:08.486 A:middle
should say, where white full,

00:19:08.896 --> 00:19:11.096 A:middle
opaque white is full transparent

00:19:11.146 --> 00:19:12.646 A:middle
and gradiating towards that is

00:19:12.726 --> 00:19:13.466 A:middle
going to give you a

00:19:13.836 --> 00:19:14.596 A:middle
transparency.

00:19:15.996 --> 00:19:18.156 A:middle
So, once we apply the vibrancy,

00:19:18.566 --> 00:19:20.476 A:middle
we can see that the gray colors

00:19:20.476 --> 00:19:23.116 A:middle
become a lot more saturated, and

00:19:23.336 --> 00:19:26.016 A:middle
the legibility of the Quaternary

00:19:26.016 --> 00:19:27.306 A:middle
Color Label is a lot more

00:19:27.306 --> 00:19:27.776 A:middle
improved.

00:19:28.386 --> 00:19:29.796 A:middle
Putting them side by side, we

00:19:29.796 --> 00:19:32.326 A:middle
can see just how much of a

00:19:32.326 --> 00:19:34.026 A:middle
difference there is between the

00:19:34.026 --> 00:19:35.776 A:middle
opacity construction, versus the

00:19:35.776 --> 00:19:36.856 A:middle
grayscale construction.

00:19:36.856 --> 00:19:39.486 A:middle
In some cases, over certain

00:19:39.486 --> 00:19:43.036 A:middle
colors, the opacity construction

00:19:43.086 --> 00:19:45.466 A:middle
will fly, but it's not exactly

00:19:45.516 --> 00:19:47.636 A:middle
the best end result,

00:19:48.196 --> 00:19:50.046 A:middle
aesthetically or legibility

00:19:50.046 --> 00:19:50.476 A:middle
wise.

00:19:52.536 --> 00:19:54.976 A:middle
Next, let's take a look at

00:19:54.976 --> 00:19:56.396 A:middle
artistically inverting glyphs,

00:19:56.856 --> 00:19:58.456 A:middle
and, by artistically inverting,

00:19:58.456 --> 00:19:59.856 A:middle
what I'm referring to is the

00:19:59.856 --> 00:20:01.856 A:middle
process of creatively looking at


00:19:59.856 --> 00:20:01.856 A:middle
process of creatively looking at

00:20:01.856 --> 00:20:03.516 A:middle
your glyphs and determining what

00:20:03.606 --> 00:20:05.316 A:middle
areas need to be adjusted to

00:20:05.356 --> 00:20:06.916 A:middle
take advantage of the Dark Mode,

00:20:08.166 --> 00:20:08.856 A:middle
for example.

00:20:09.546 --> 00:20:11.876 A:middle
So, here we've got a set of our

00:20:11.996 --> 00:20:13.566 A:middle
standard glyphs that we have in

00:20:13.566 --> 00:20:14.216 A:middle
the light appearance.

00:20:14.876 --> 00:20:16.106 A:middle
One thing to note is that the

00:20:16.106 --> 00:20:17.726 A:middle
light appearances glyphs

00:20:18.166 --> 00:20:20.716 A:middle
generally use a lot of edge

00:20:20.716 --> 00:20:22.996 A:middle
strokes with hollow centers.

00:20:23.386 --> 00:20:24.406 A:middle
And the reason for that is that

00:20:24.406 --> 00:20:25.746 A:middle
we take advantage of the white

00:20:25.816 --> 00:20:27.186 A:middle
backgrounds that these are

00:20:27.186 --> 00:20:29.156 A:middle
generally placed on top of in

00:20:29.156 --> 00:20:32.086 A:middle
order to denote form and shape.

00:20:33.136 --> 00:20:34.826 A:middle
But, if we were to take these

00:20:34.826 --> 00:20:36.736 A:middle
exact same vector forms and

00:20:36.996 --> 00:20:38.246 A:middle
place them over a dark

00:20:38.296 --> 00:20:40.196 A:middle
background, all of that sense of

00:20:40.426 --> 00:20:42.606 A:middle
form and volume is kind of lost,

00:20:43.206 --> 00:20:44.666 A:middle
and so we had to artistically

00:20:44.666 --> 00:20:46.526 A:middle
invert them to bring back some

00:20:46.526 --> 00:20:47.766 A:middle
of that sense of form and

00:20:47.766 --> 00:20:48.306 A:middle
volume.

00:20:50.286 --> 00:20:51.976 A:middle
Looking at how some of these are

00:20:51.976 --> 00:20:53.916 A:middle
constructed, we've got a couple

00:20:53.916 --> 00:20:55.206 A:middle
of simple examples, like this

00:20:55.206 --> 00:20:55.606 A:middle
finder tag.

00:20:55.606 --> 00:20:58.886 A:middle
On the left side, it's denoting

00:20:58.886 --> 00:21:00.826 A:middle
a white tag with a dark eyelet


00:20:58.886 --> 00:21:00.826 A:middle
a white tag with a dark eyelet

00:21:00.946 --> 00:21:01.346 A:middle
cutout.

00:21:01.936 --> 00:21:03.286 A:middle
On the right side, however, in

00:21:03.286 --> 00:21:05.406 A:middle
Dark Mode, that sense of it

00:21:05.406 --> 00:21:06.976 A:middle
being a white sheet of paper is

00:21:06.976 --> 00:21:07.336 A:middle
lost.

00:21:07.816 --> 00:21:09.636 A:middle
So, once we invert it, we get

00:21:09.636 --> 00:21:10.936 A:middle
back that white sheet of paper

00:21:10.966 --> 00:21:13.126 A:middle
with an eyelet knockout hole.

00:21:14.286 --> 00:21:15.386 A:middle
Looking at how this is

00:21:15.386 --> 00:21:18.976 A:middle
constructed, generally, what you

00:21:19.546 --> 00:21:23.056 A:middle
would do is expand the clipping

00:21:23.056 --> 00:21:24.686 A:middle
paths, I should say, and then

00:21:24.906 --> 00:21:27.416 A:middle
select your eyelet shape and

00:21:27.416 --> 00:21:28.756 A:middle
then reverse the knockout on

00:21:29.506 --> 00:21:29.606 A:middle
that.

00:21:29.606 --> 00:21:31.006 A:middle
And then it's just a game of

00:21:31.046 --> 00:21:35.386 A:middle
selecting any redundant vector

00:21:35.386 --> 00:21:38.896 A:middle
paths and removing those.

00:21:38.946 --> 00:21:40.896 A:middle
Taking a look at a slightly more

00:21:41.156 --> 00:21:42.856 A:middle
complex shape, for example, the

00:21:42.856 --> 00:21:43.226 A:middle
house.

00:21:43.766 --> 00:21:46.246 A:middle
We've got a white house on the

00:21:46.246 --> 00:21:47.396 A:middle
left side, and on the right

00:21:47.426 --> 00:21:48.566 A:middle
side, the house isn't white

00:21:48.566 --> 00:21:48.996 A:middle
anymore.

00:21:49.616 --> 00:21:52.056 A:middle
So, inverting it returns us back

00:21:52.106 --> 00:21:54.936 A:middle
to a white painted house.

00:21:56.096 --> 00:21:57.196 A:middle
Generally, the construction for

00:21:57.196 --> 00:21:58.626 A:middle
this is about the same as the

00:21:58.626 --> 00:22:02.376 A:middle
other process, but one important


00:21:58.626 --> 00:22:02.376 A:middle
other process, but one important

00:22:02.596 --> 00:22:04.066 A:middle
aspect of this glyph, in

00:22:04.066 --> 00:22:06.316 A:middle
particular, was that we have to

00:22:06.356 --> 00:22:09.116 A:middle
add a new shape into the vector

00:22:09.116 --> 00:22:09.536 A:middle
form.

00:22:09.846 --> 00:22:11.036 A:middle
In this case, we're mimicking

00:22:11.036 --> 00:22:13.646 A:middle
the roof line, creating a shadow

00:22:13.646 --> 00:22:15.326 A:middle
underneath the roof that we're

00:22:15.326 --> 00:22:17.286 A:middle
going to knock out.

00:22:17.416 --> 00:22:18.646 A:middle
And this is important, because

00:22:18.646 --> 00:22:20.826 A:middle
if we were to have left the

00:22:20.826 --> 00:22:21.816 A:middle
construction of the house

00:22:21.816 --> 00:22:23.706 A:middle
without that shadow line, the

00:22:23.706 --> 00:22:25.186 A:middle
roof would have no definition,

00:22:25.186 --> 00:22:26.136 A:middle
and it would be really hard to

00:22:26.136 --> 00:22:27.586 A:middle
see that at small size.

00:22:29.936 --> 00:22:32.156 A:middle
Moving on to a more complicated

00:22:32.586 --> 00:22:35.056 A:middle
glyph, like this mail envelope,

00:22:35.056 --> 00:22:35.666 A:middle
for example.

00:22:36.136 --> 00:22:37.646 A:middle
On the left side, we can see a

00:22:37.686 --> 00:22:38.986 A:middle
sense of volume and shape.

00:22:38.986 --> 00:22:41.086 A:middle
We've got two layers, generally.

00:22:41.126 --> 00:22:42.656 A:middle
We've got the back flap of the

00:22:42.656 --> 00:22:43.626 A:middle
envelope, and we've got the

00:22:43.626 --> 00:22:45.696 A:middle
front flap of the envelope with

00:22:45.696 --> 00:22:47.026 A:middle
a letter contained in between.

00:22:47.426 --> 00:22:48.876 A:middle
On the right side, a lot of that

00:22:48.876 --> 00:22:50.456 A:middle
sense of volume is just missing

00:22:50.456 --> 00:22:52.466 A:middle
because of the lack of fill

00:22:52.556 --> 00:22:53.096 A:middle
colors.

00:22:54.066 --> 00:22:56.306 A:middle
And so, once we invert that, we

00:22:56.306 --> 00:22:57.576 A:middle
return back to having a sense of

00:22:57.576 --> 00:22:57.956 A:middle
volume.

00:22:59.906 --> 00:23:01.736 A:middle
Again, generally, the process of


00:22:59.906 --> 00:23:01.736 A:middle
Again, generally, the process of

00:23:01.776 --> 00:23:03.436 A:middle
construction for this one is

00:23:03.436 --> 00:23:04.406 A:middle
about the same as some of the

00:23:04.406 --> 00:23:06.706 A:middle
other ones, but it's a little

00:23:06.706 --> 00:23:10.246 A:middle
bit more detailed and time

00:23:10.246 --> 00:23:12.066 A:middle
consuming just due to the number

00:23:12.066 --> 00:23:13.106 A:middle
of paths that there are.

00:23:13.196 --> 00:23:14.866 A:middle
But, generally, what you want to

00:23:14.866 --> 00:23:16.116 A:middle
do is break it apart into two

00:23:16.116 --> 00:23:17.816 A:middle
pieces, again, so that you have

00:23:17.816 --> 00:23:19.256 A:middle
the front and the rear portion,

00:23:19.506 --> 00:23:20.936 A:middle
and then you have your letter

00:23:20.936 --> 00:23:21.956 A:middle
portion in between.

00:23:22.616 --> 00:23:24.636 A:middle
One important detail that this

00:23:24.676 --> 00:23:29.026 A:middle
glyph exemplifies is the dual

00:23:29.026 --> 00:23:30.756 A:middle
opacities that we use in some of

00:23:30.756 --> 00:23:31.146 A:middle
our glyphs.

00:23:31.336 --> 00:23:32.696 A:middle
In this case, the letter is set

00:23:32.786 --> 00:23:35.536 A:middle
to 80% opacity in order to make

00:23:35.536 --> 00:23:36.956 A:middle
it secondary to the envelope,

00:23:36.956 --> 00:23:38.316 A:middle
itself, being opened, which is

00:23:38.316 --> 00:23:38.876 A:middle
what we're trying to

00:23:38.906 --> 00:23:39.486 A:middle
communicate.

00:23:40.406 --> 00:23:42.026 A:middle
And the opposite is true in

00:23:42.026 --> 00:23:43.756 A:middle
Light Mode also, where we do use

00:23:43.896 --> 00:23:45.906 A:middle
80% opacities, in some cases,

00:23:45.906 --> 00:23:46.406 A:middle
also.

00:23:48.176 --> 00:23:50.796 A:middle
So, quickly wrapping up what

00:23:50.796 --> 00:23:51.846 A:middle
we've covered so far.

00:23:52.906 --> 00:23:55.646 A:middle
Dark interfaces are cool, so

00:23:55.646 --> 00:23:56.876 A:middle
cool that you're probably going

00:23:56.876 --> 00:23:57.986 A:middle
to want to make your app

00:23:58.386 --> 00:23:59.886 A:middle
potentially dark all the time,

00:23:59.946 --> 00:24:01.016 A:middle
but unless your app is a


00:23:59.946 --> 00:24:01.016 A:middle
but unless your app is a

00:24:01.116 --> 00:24:03.436 A:middle
creative or media-centric app,

00:24:03.436 --> 00:24:05.016 A:middle
you should reconsider that, and,

00:24:05.016 --> 00:24:06.656 A:middle
instead make your app follow

00:24:06.656 --> 00:24:07.666 A:middle
what the system appearance is

00:24:07.696 --> 00:24:08.586 A:middle
set to, instead.

00:24:09.396 --> 00:24:12.476 A:middle
Don't limit your app design to

00:24:12.646 --> 00:24:14.396 A:middle
just inverting your existing

00:24:14.396 --> 00:24:15.846 A:middle
light appearance, and, instead,

00:24:16.016 --> 00:24:18.086 A:middle
take a look at what elements are

00:24:18.086 --> 00:24:20.556 A:middle
in your app on a case-by-case

00:24:20.626 --> 00:24:22.266 A:middle
basis, and try and determine

00:24:22.266 --> 00:24:23.896 A:middle
what are the visual cues that

00:24:23.896 --> 00:24:26.076 A:middle
are trying to be communicated by

00:24:26.076 --> 00:24:27.806 A:middle
the controls, and then determine

00:24:27.806 --> 00:24:29.116 A:middle
whether an opposite visual cue

00:24:29.116 --> 00:24:33.206 A:middle
is necessary or not.

00:24:33.206 --> 00:24:34.846 A:middle
Then take a look at what type of

00:24:34.886 --> 00:24:36.806 A:middle
content your app produces or

00:24:36.806 --> 00:24:39.836 A:middle
displays, and then use that as a

00:24:39.836 --> 00:24:42.116 A:middle
guidance to determine what type

00:24:42.356 --> 00:24:44.136 A:middle
of method to use for how to

00:24:44.136 --> 00:24:45.336 A:middle
treat your content area--

00:24:45.686 --> 00:24:46.886 A:middle
whether to go fully dark,

00:24:47.406 --> 00:24:49.826 A:middle
whether to make it stay as is,

00:24:49.936 --> 00:24:51.076 A:middle
or whether to make it a user

00:24:51.076 --> 00:24:52.716 A:middle
option via the app settings.

00:24:54.436 --> 00:24:57.106 A:middle
Then, taking a look at colors,

00:24:58.986 --> 00:25:02.026 A:middle
generally, you want to make sure


00:24:58.986 --> 00:25:02.026 A:middle
generally, you want to make sure

00:25:02.026 --> 00:25:03.526 A:middle
that you're using the three

00:25:03.526 --> 00:25:04.666 A:middle
colors that we went over,

00:25:04.666 --> 00:25:05.786 A:middle
appropriately, if you have

00:25:05.876 --> 00:25:07.956 A:middle
controls that are text controls,

00:25:08.406 --> 00:25:11.026 A:middle
try using text link if it's

00:25:11.026 --> 00:25:11.806 A:middle
applicable.

00:25:12.306 --> 00:25:13.746 A:middle
If you have controls that you

00:25:13.746 --> 00:25:16.176 A:middle
want to follow the system accent

00:25:16.216 --> 00:25:18.746 A:middle
color appearance, set those to

00:25:19.286 --> 00:25:20.736 A:middle
control accent color, and if you

00:25:20.736 --> 00:25:21.866 A:middle
have a control that has to stay

00:25:21.866 --> 00:25:24.626 A:middle
blue all the time, adopt system

00:25:24.626 --> 00:25:25.756 A:middle
blue color.

00:25:25.756 --> 00:25:27.976 A:middle
And then Taylor and Rachel are

00:25:27.976 --> 00:25:29.576 A:middle
going to go into a lot more

00:25:29.576 --> 00:25:30.986 A:middle
detail about color uses, so

00:25:31.236 --> 00:25:32.916 A:middle
definitely pay attention to

00:25:32.916 --> 00:25:33.986 A:middle
their section.

00:25:34.646 --> 00:25:37.686 A:middle
When constructing your vibrancy

00:25:37.686 --> 00:25:39.226 A:middle
areas, make sure that you're

00:25:39.226 --> 00:25:40.856 A:middle
constructing them in a way that

00:25:40.856 --> 00:25:42.186 A:middle
takes full advantage of the

00:25:42.186 --> 00:25:44.046 A:middle
vibrant effect blending, so make

00:25:44.046 --> 00:25:45.206 A:middle
sure that you're using grayscale

00:25:45.206 --> 00:25:46.236 A:middle
colors that are opaque.

00:25:46.316 --> 00:25:47.966 A:middle
And if you have areas that need

00:25:47.966 --> 00:25:50.066 A:middle
to be knockouts or have

00:25:50.066 --> 00:25:52.646 A:middle
opacities, ramp towards black in

00:25:52.646 --> 00:25:54.246 A:middle
Dark Mode or ramp towards white

00:25:54.386 --> 00:25:55.026 A:middle
in Light Mode.

00:25:56.476 --> 00:26:00.056 A:middle
And then, lastly, make sure that


00:25:56.476 --> 00:26:00.056 A:middle
And then, lastly, make sure that

00:26:00.056 --> 00:26:01.666 A:middle
the glyphs that you're using are

00:26:01.736 --> 00:26:03.666 A:middle
artistically inverted in order

00:26:03.746 --> 00:26:07.386 A:middle
to showcase the intent that the

00:26:07.386 --> 00:26:08.746 A:middle
glyphs are trying to communicate

